name: Farm Fresh Zucchini Cranberry Nut Muffins
author: SHORECOOK
summary: Steve, my farmer friend, has kept me well supplied with zucchini. I was looking to make an original muffin recipe to thank him that would knock his socks off.
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C)
Mix 6 tablespoons flour and brown sugar together in a bowl for topping; cut butter into the flour mixture until you have pea-sized crumbs
Beat margarine and white sugar with an electric mixer in a large bowl until light and fluffy
Beat egg and vanilla into the butter mixture
Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt together in a separate bowl; gradually beat into the butter mixture
Fold zucchini, cranberries, and walnuts into the mixture; spoon into prepared muffin cups, filling nearly to the top
Sprinkle reserved topping mixture onto the batter
Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, about 25 minutes
